model

Class Booking

  • Object
    • Booking

  • public class Booking
extends Object
    A booking for a seat. The information stored in a booking object includes the number of the booked seat, the customer who made the booking, the price category and the price of the booking.

    To favor code safety, booking objects are immutable: all field values are specified at construction time and cannot be modified later on.

    Note to DataAccess implementors:
    As an option, a booking can be identified by an ID - a positive int value - specified at construction time. It is the responsibility of the caller to ensure that IDs are unique across all bookings. If you use this feature, make sure all Booking objects have an ID: Booking objects with and without an ID cannot be mixed.
